7.4 \times 10^{-6}$, the maximum slope-direction stresses are respectively 0.88MPa and 0.77MPa, as shown in Figure 16. The minimum crack resistance safety factors between days 4 to 7 for these two scenarios are respectively 1.83 and 2.20. Using concrete with a smaller linear expansion coefficient is more effective for crack prevention in the panel.
